The destructuring `{ text = 'Default' }` sets a fallback value of 'Default' for the text prop. When the component is used with no props, text falls back to 'Default', so the rendered output is <span>Default</span>.

function Label({ text = 'Default' }) {
  return <span>{text}</span>;
}

